	<content:heading>Statically Typed</content:heading>
	
	<p>A statically typed language is one where variables have explicit types associated with them. This allows <content:tt>program verification</content:tt> and efficient execution since the exact type of data is known at compile time.</p>
	
	<p>Statically typed languages are often <content:tt>compiled</content:tt> but not always.</p>
	
